# Semgrep ignore — applied by self-semgrep.yml when it scans this repo.
#
# `semgrep-self-test.yml` already runs the rule unit tests against
# fixtures under `semgrep-scan/tests/`; those fixtures are intentionally
# rule-violating (curl|sh, eval, rm -rf /, script-injection patterns)
# so the rule-validation harness can assert positives. They should NOT
# be reported as findings by the *full-repo* self-scan.
#
# Same reasoning for `semgrep-scan/rules/` itself: the rule files quote
# the very patterns they detect (e.g. `pattern-regex:` lines containing
# `curl|sh`), so naive scanning matches them too.
semgrep-scan/tests/
semgrep-scan/rules/
